AI Reviewer

Project Brief: AI Reviewer (AIR)
Objective: A serverless, multi-tenant GitHub App that uses AI to perform automated code reviews on Pull Requests. The app demonstrates senior-level architectural patterns including event-driven processing and granular RBAC.

Tech Stack:

Framework: Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript

Auth & Identity: Clerk (Organization-based RBAC)

Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL) with Prisma ORM

Async Processing: Inngest (Background job orchestration for AI tasks)

IDE/Tools: Cursor (for development)

Core Architecture (Option B: GitHub App Model):

Multi-Tenancy: The app is installed at the GitHub Organization level. Access is controlled via an installation_id stored in Supabase.

Webhook Flow: GitHub sends pull_request events to a Next.js Route Handler. The handler validates the signature and hands off the payload to Inngest.

User Roles:

Superuser: Platform management and global health.

Admin: Manages organization-wide repo access, user permissions, and billing.

Team Lead: Configures AI strictness/rules for specific collections of repos.

Developer: Views and interacts with AI feedback on PRs.

Database Strategy: Prisma schema mapping Users to Organizations and Repositories with specific permission claims.

Immediate Goal: Set up the GitHub App handshake using a Manifest flow, establish a local tunnel for webhooks, and initialize the Prisma schema to handle Organizations, Repositories, and UserPermissions.

