Prisma model (high level)
User — clerkUserId, optional email, isSuperuser for platform operators.
Organization — githubInstallationId (string), optional clerkOrganizationId, name/slug.
OrganizationMember — OrganizationRole: ADMIN | TEAM_LEAD | DEVELOPER**, unique per org + user.
Repository — tied to org; GitHub ids, fullName, privacy, default branch.
RepositoryScope — optional per-user repo claims; canConfigure for team leads on specific repos (admins can be treated as “all repos” in app logic).
Supabase + Prisma commonly use a pooled DATABASE_URL and a direct DIRECT_URL for migrations; both are in .env.example.

